Date: 16 Dec 2011
Source: Boston.com ledited]
http://www.boston.com/news/local/rhode_island/articles/2011/12/16/ri_health_officials_say_11_treated_for_rabies/?rss_id=Boston.com+--+Rhode+Island+news

RI health officials say 11 treated for rabies

Smithfield, R.I.-Eleven people in Rhode Island have been treated for
rabies as a precaution after a pet cat tested positive for the
disease. The cat lived with its owners in Smithfield. It had signs of
rabies when it died.

The people treated are all known to have come into contact with the
cat. One dog has also undergone treatment.

State officials say anyone else in the area of Birch Road in
Smithfield should contact the state health department if they have had
contact with the female orange-grey calico cat. State health officials
say the case shows the importance of vaccinating cats and dogs against
rabies.
